    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
      "source": "Now, you can explore the map by zoom-in/out the marked areas\n, and try to answer the following questions:\n\n*   Are all launch sites in proximity to the Equator line?\n*   Are all launch sites in very close proximity to the coast?\n\nAlso please try to explain your findings.\n",
      "metadata": {}
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "source": "#Are all launch sites close to the Equator?\n #Not exactly. They’re not on the Equator, but they are relatively low-latitude compared to northern U.S. locations. Florida sites are closer to the Equator than VAFB in California.\n\n#Are all launch sites close to the coast?\n#Yes. All launch sites are very close to the coastline.\n\n#Why?\n#Launching near the coast is safer because rockets can fly over the ocean instead of populated areas. Being closer to the Equator can also help because Earth’s rotation gives rockets a little extra speed boost.\n\n# Task 2: Mark the success/failed launches for each site on the map\n\n",
      "metadata": {
        "trusted": true
      },
      "outputs": [],
      "execution_count": 19
    },
    {
      "cell_type": "markdown",
